  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cushing's disease is a rare serious condition that is caused by an adrenocorticotropic
      hormone (ACTH) secreting pituitary adenoma. This study will assess the long-term safety and
      efficacy of pasireotide in patients with Cushing's disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
